docs.snippet: Within the next few days the International Wheat Council will convene in Washington to begin deliberations on a question which vitally concerns the direction of American farm policy. That is the question of whether the international wheat agreement...
docs.lead_paragraph: Within the next few days the International Wheat Council will convene in Washington to begin deliberations on a question which vitally concerns the direction of American farm policy. That is the question of whether the international wheat agreement of 1949, scheduled to expire on July 31, next, is to be extended, presumptively for another four years.

docs.snippet: Drafts owed United States exporters by Brazilian traders continued to increase last month, rising $2,200,000 to a new high of $202,900,000, according to the Federal Reserve Bank of New York. The data, based on reports from fifteen banks which...
docs.lead_paragraph: Drafts owed United States exporters by Brazilian traders continued to increase last month, rising $2,200,000 to a new high of $202,900,000, according to the Federal Reserve Bank of New York. The data, based on reports from fifteen banks which participate in a monthly export credit survey, showed that new drawings on Brazilian importers as well as drafts paid by them rose moderately to $7,100,000, and $4,900,000, respectively.
